    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-01T16:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-01T16:30:00-05:00" n="751"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.857/68: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-01T17:00:00-04:30"
                            >March 1, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Your 14, February 29, 4 p.m. Dr. Gil Borges<note n="32" xml:id="d751fn32"
                        >Esteban Gil Borges, Venezuelan Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> feels
                    that the American position may be weakened if a protest is made before statutes
                    for the government of the continental security zone have been drawn up and
                    accepted by the 21 republics. He doubts that by this criterion the <hi
                        rend="italic">Wakama</hi> incident would constitute a violation. However,
                    the Foreign Minister will not advise his Government to hold back from a
                    collective action provided all have agreed, and he has promised the Embassy a
                    written statement of its position after conferring with the President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
